'''Manuel Pardiñas Serrano''' was a [[Spain|Spanish]] [[anarchism|anarchist]] who assassinated [[José Canalejas (politician)|José Canalejas]], the [[Prime Minister of Spain]]. Pardiñas shot Canalejas in front of the San Martín Library in [[Madrid]] on November 12, 1912. Pardiñas then turned the gun on himself and committed suicide. He was reportedly from the town of [[El Grado]] in the [[province of Huesca]].<ref>{{cite news | title = Anarchist Kills Spain's Premier; Inspired by Ferrer Execution, Youth Shoots Canalejas in a Madrid Square. | date = 13 November 1912 | url = https://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9C03E6D8133CE633A25750C1A9679D946396D6CF | newspaper = [[The New York Times]] | publisher = | accessdate = 17 July 2010 | ref = | first=Dispatch | last=To}} </ref>
