'''Rose Constance Owusu''' is a [[Ghanaian]] former Justice of the [[Supreme Court of Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghana.gov.gh/index.php/news/1545-president-swears-in-two-supreme-court-judges|title=President Swears In Two Supreme Court Judges - Government of Ghana|last=Jotie|first=Sule|website=www.ghana.gov.gh|access-date=2016-09-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.graphic.com.gh/news/politics/how-the-judges-ruled-3.html|title=How the judges ruled (3) - Graphic Online - {{!}} 2016|last=Jasmine|first=Arku|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-09-05}}</ref><ref name=retires>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/NewsArchive/SC-Justice-Rose-Constance-Owusu-retires-319656|title=SC Justice Rose Constance Owusu retires|website=GhanaWeb|date=3 August 2014|access-date=2016-09-05}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Rose Owusu had her legal training at the [[University of Ghana]], where she earned her [[LLB]], and at the [[Ghana School of Law]], where she had her Qualifying Certificate.
Before becoming a judge, Owusu worked at the Attorney General's Department, rising through the ranks to the position of Chief State Attorney.<ref name=retires />
==Personal life== Rose Owusu is a Christian.
