{{primary sources|date=April 2015}} '''Shakti Gawain''' (30 September 1948 – 11 November 2018) was a [[New Age]] and [[personal development]] author.<ref>[http://www.shaktigawain.com/about Gawain Biog]</ref> Her books have sold over 10 million copies.<ref name="PubWeek">{{cite news|last1=Bond|first1=Gwenda|title=Inspirational and Spirituality Books 2014: Getting Centered|url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/by-topic/new-titles/adult-announcements/article/61731-getting-centered-inspirational-and-spirituality-books.html|accessdate=12 March 2016|work=[[Publishers Weekly]]|date=4 April 2014}}</ref>
==Background== Born Carol Louisa Gawain, she graduated from the [[University of California]] with a degree in fine arts and dance in the mid 1970s.<ref>[http://www.shaktigawain.com/ Shakti Gawain personal website]</ref>
Gawain's best known book is ''Creative Visualization: Use the Power of Your Imagination to Create What You Want in Life'' (1978).<ref>[http://www.shareguide.com/Gawain.html Share Guide]</ref> It has been a bestselling book for nearly 40 years.<ref name="Yahoo">{{cite news|last1=Callahan|first1=Maggie|title=Visualization: The Power Of Positive Thought|url=https://www.yahoo.com/beauty/visualization-the-power-of-positive-1303664840015926.html|accessdate=12 March 2016|work=[[Yahoo! News]]|date=20 November 2015}}</ref> The book was said to have inspired [[Des'ree]]'s 1994 hit song "[[You Gotta Be]]". Gawain was the co-founder, with Marc Allen, of New World Library Publishing Company<ref>[http://www.newworldlibrary.com/ New World Library]</ref> and founder of Nataraj Publishing, a division of New World Library.
Gawain and her husband, Jim Burns, divided their time between [[California]] and [[Hawaii]]. Her father was a professor at a military academy in Northern California. Her mother, Elizabeth M. Gawain (born 1921), was a city planner for HUD in Washington DC in the 1970s.
