==Club career== On February 12, 2011, Hammar made his professional debut for [[AS Nancy]] in a [[Ligue 1]] game against [[AJ Auxerre]]. Hammar started the game on the bench and came on as a substitute in the 89th minute in place of [[Alexandre Cuvillier]], as Nancy went on to win 3-1.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheMatch30828_198117.html|title=Nancy 3-1 Auxerre , Ligue 1 - 23e journée , Football|website=www.lequipe.fr|language=fr|access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lfp.fr/ligue1/feuille_match/53843?live=1|title=LIVE - Ligue 1 Conforama - Saison 2010/2011 - 23ème journée - AS Nancy Lorraine / AJ Auxerre|website=www.lfp.fr|language=fr|access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref>
Before the 2013-2014 [[Süper Lig]] season, Hammar moved to [[Kayseri Erciyesspor]]. He played his first match for his new team in a [[Turkish Cup]] meeting against [[Edirnespor]].
==International career== Hammar was a member of the [[Algeria national under-17 football team|Algerian Under-17 National Team]] at the [[2009 FIFA U-17 World Cup]] in [[Nigeria]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldfootball/statisticsandrecords/players/player=314394/index.html|title=FIFA Tournaments - Players & Coaches - Ziri HAMMAR|website=FIFA.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-05-25}}</ref> He played in all three of Algeria's group stage games at the World Cup, coming on as a substitute in the first two and starting the final one against South Korea. However, Algeria lost all three games and failed to progress to the second round.
On March 24, 2010, Hammar was called up to the [[Algeria national under-20 football team|Algerian Under-20 National Team]] for the [[2010 UNAF U-20 Tournament]] in [[Algeria]].<ref>[http://www.dzfoot.com/news-6144/en-u20-la-selection-pour-le-tournoi-de-l-unaf/ EN U20 : La sélection pour le tournoi de l'UNAF] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815204142/http://www.dzfoot.com/news-6144/en-u20-la-selection-pour-le-tournoi-de-l-unaf/ |date=August 15, 2011 }}</ref>
